    "body": "### Description\n\nHello guys,\nI've been using `LSP[basedpyright]` for four months, and until I updated to the most recent version a few days ago—I don't update frequently—I hadn't run into this error.\n\nThe error:\n```\nLSP[basedpyright] Error returned from file system watcher: Error: ENOSPC: System limit for number of file watchers reached, watch '/home/user/dev/data/folder/file.txt'\n```\n\nThis is my configuration for this LSP; note that I'm using `NvChad`:\n```\nlspconfig.basedpyright.setup {\n  on_attach = nvlsp.on_attach,\n  on_init = nvlsp.on_init,\n  capabilities = nvlsp.capabilities,\n  settings = {\n    basedpyright = {\n      analysis = {\n        typeCheckingMode = \"standard\",\n        exclude = {\"**/data/**/*\"},\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\nI thought using `exclude` would avoid `basedpyright` to look into this kind of folder, but the error still presists. (I have also tried `ignore`, but I don't think it's the right parameter)\n\n\nSpec:\n`NVIM v0.10.4`\n`Ubuntu 24.04.1 LTS`",
